article.headline: Northern Arizona 91, Idaho State 72
article.story: CHENEY, Wash. (AP) -- Aaron Bond scored 24 points as Northern Arizona beat Idaho State 91-72 in the semifinals of the Big Sky Conference basketball tournament on Tuesday. Second-seeded Northern Arizona (15-13) will play the survivor of Tuesday night's Weber State-Eastern Washington game on Wednesday, with the winner earning the Big Sky's automatic bid into the NCAA tournament. Northern Arizona last made the NCAAs in 2000. Marquis Poole led Idaho State (13-18), the No. 3 seed, with 23 points. Poole led the Big Sky this year with 18.8 points per game. Scott Henry added 17 for the Bengals. Northern Arizona's Joakim Kjellbom, a 7-foot center, tied the school record with six blocked shots. He added 13 points and 10 rebounds as the Lumberjacks dominated the rebounding 39-28. With the score tied at 9, Kelly Golob's 3-pointer triggered a 14-2 Northern Arizona run that built a 23-11 lead with 9:51 left in the first. Golob finished with 21 points. Consecutive 3-pointers by Bond, who scored 16 in the first half, extended the lead to 34-17. The Lumberjacks led 47-33 at halftime. Bond, a 6-foot-7 senior, scored eight points in the first three minutes of the second half as Northern Arizona took a 57-38 lead. He shot 5 of 8 from 3-point range Northern Arizona, which beat Montana in overtime in the final game of the regular season to qualify for the tournament, beat Idaho State twice during the regular season.
